  "body": "We have several procedures in the application which require additional authentication, e.g.:\r\n- Change password\r\n- Add wallet account\r\n- Sync new device\r\n\r\nCurrently all of those procedures have their own password input to authenticate.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1083\" alt=\"Снимок экрана 2022-06-15 в 20 09 39\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25482501/173887847-12411b01-297d-440f-83d0-c473e2cac73b.png\">\r\n\r\nBut there should be a unique workflow component for that, which would consider different methods of authentications, such as:\r\n- password\r\n- biometric (technically, this is when the password is stored in a secure enclave, and the OS biometrics release the password)\r\n- keycard + pin\r\n- keycard + biometric (technically, this is when the pin is stored in a secure enclave, and the OS biometrics release the pin)\r\n\r\nThis component should be reused wherever it's needed.\r\n\r\nIt could probably be an Embeddable component, or a standalone Popup, depending on the way it's used.\r\nBut it seems we don't actually have a defined designs for that.\r\nBut `Sync New Device` designs seems to have to closest variant.\r\n\r\nDesign links:\r\n- [Sync new device](https://www.figma.com/file/idUoxN7OIW2Jpp3PMJ1Rl8/%E2%9A%99%EF%B8%8F-Settings-%7C-Desktop?node-id=1592%3A128969)\r\n- [Change Password](https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=2203%3A237514)\r\n- [Add Wallet Account](https://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?node-id=5248%3A188817)",
